1
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:37,245
<i>Do you know where our child is?</i>

2
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:40,874
She might be in Cebu
with our future in-laws.

3
00:00:40,957 --> 00:00:43,626
<i>Mario and Tess</i>
<i>are not returning our calls.</i>

4
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,087
<i>We should reach out to them aggressively.</i>

5
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:48,381
<i>Let's give them a grand emmisary.</i>

6
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:51,468
<i>You're the one</i>
<i>who had a lot of doubts in Mikoy.</i>

7
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:56,181
But you still believe
that we should find him and save him.

8
00:00:56,264 --> 00:01:00,393
I think there's only one place
where they know where Mikoy is.

9
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:03,938
Cebu.

10
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:13,031
I was the last person La Fornarina
spoke to before she disappeared.

11
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:17,368
Say hello to Marga Espinosa
and Dasho Malabanan.

12
00:01:18,161 --> 00:01:20,830
Why? Do you want to be like that?

13
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:27,587
I want to, but it seems impossible.

14
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:31,674
<i>Our relationship survived</i>
<i>in the midst of pretending.</i>

15
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:33,593
Whatever happens,

16
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:36,346
there's always tomorrow that awaits us.

17
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:42,268
In-laws! How have you been?

18
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:58,785
What brings you here so suddenly?

19
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:01,663
Sorry, we weren't able
to let you know sooner.

20
00:02:02,205 --> 00:02:04,207
Mario, Tess.

21
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,918
We're in-laws, aren't we?

22
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:11,714
It's been a while since we experienced
the Pinagpala hospitality.

23
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,842
We've missed you so much.

24
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:26,187
Just the two of us.

25
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:50,044
That can only mean two things.

26
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:54,090
First, Viktor is here to fish
for information from the Pinagpalas,

27
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:58,136
or Viktor is bringing them information.

28
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,598
Either way, we don't have access
to that information.

29
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,434
Whether it's from Mario or from Viktor.

30
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,102
I have an idea.

31
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:09,856
I know what we're going to do
so we can get the information ourselves

32
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:11,566
through their family.

33
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:16,154
How have you been, in-law?

34
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,075
Leave us alone for a moment.

35
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:24,120
‪Well.

36
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,709
I'm okay. Life goes on.

37
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:33,922
Even with things happening
that I can't control.

38
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:40,345
As for me,
I've been having trouble sleeping.

39
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:43,640
Donabel says

40
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:45,892
my skin is getting dry.

41
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:49,020
But yours

42
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:53,107
still look fresh. How?

43
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,278
You know, in-law.

44
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,781
I already know the truth.

45
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:05,536
So we don't need to talk about the thing
we're not supposed to talk about.

46
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,455
I understand that we shouldn't

47
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:10,541
talk about the things
that shouldn't be discussed.

48
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,752
Well, in-law, no matter what happens,

49
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,297
you still need to take care of yourself.

50
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:22,971
I mean,

51
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:25,306
how many steps is it?

52
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:30,186
Viktor, stop beating around the bush.

53
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,397
What is it really?

54
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:37,443
But in-law, I'm really shocked.

55
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:40,071
How were you able to get into that?

56
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:42,573
The thing that we're not
allowed to talk about.

57
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,623
nor deny what you're calling

58
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:53,710
the thing that shouldn't be discussed.

59
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:09,600
I don't know what you've heard about me.

60
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:14,939
Maybe some of those things are true.

61
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:21,154
But for sure, many of them
are just exaggerations.

62
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:25,616
in-law.

63
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:33,916
is I'm not the enemy of my own child.

64
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,962
And I'm not the enemy of the person

65
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:40,798
she loves the most.

66
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:44,093
I'm an ally here.

67
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:48,723
An ally?

68
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:53,227
You know, whether it's true or not,

69
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,688
I'm not here to judge you, in-law.

70
00:05:56,272 --> 00:06:00,193
But if the opportunity comes,
maybe you can finally

71
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,696
turn your back on that thing
we're not allowed to talk about.

72
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,907
If only life were that simple,

73
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:09,827
as if it were a hot potato
you could just spit out.

74
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,079
Right?

75
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:13,831
It's not that simple, in-law.

76
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:17,126
So let's stop talking about
what shouldn't be discussed.

77
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:34,560
And they never stop
trying to bring me down.

78
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:56,374
You know, here's my point.

79
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:59,585
Even if I don't agree
with the life you've chosen,

80
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:01,629
that thing we're not supposed to discuss,

81
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:02,672
as a mother,

82
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:05,883
we need to talk about
what we're not supposed to talk about.

83
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:10,263
Because you know,
Mikoy truly loves Chiara.

84
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:13,266
And my only obligation as a parent

85
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,184
is to understand him, right?

86
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,688
Because he knew the complications

87
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:21,774
of the life he entered.
The one we're not allowed to discuss.

88
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,026
Well.

89
00:07:25,361 --> 00:07:28,322
You know, I'm sorry, in-law,
but as of today,

90
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:30,450
I still haven't spoken to Mikoy.

91
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:33,077
That's quite strange.

92
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:34,954
Very strange.

93
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:36,789
Well,

94
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:39,750
we can sing
all the Eraserhead songs you want,

95
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:43,129
but that's the truth.

96
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:45,006
I still haven't spoken to Mikoy.

97
00:07:45,089 --> 00:07:46,591
I don't even know

98
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:50,261
where Mikoy is. Or…

99
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:54,307
I don't know where Mikoy and Chiara is.

100
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:46,776
We need to talk about the things
that have not been discussed.

101
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:48,819
What are we not supposed to talk about?

102
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,136
Sweetheart. Are you okay?

103
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,137
I can't relax.

104
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:59,640
Why? Is there a problem?

105
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:15,740
Oh.

106
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:20,995
You know…

107
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:27,710
I've noticed that we must be
really special to you.

108
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:28,711
Imagine

109
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,631
that you've got another
special delivery of your…

110
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:33,633
torta.

111
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:36,594
Of course, sir. This is a special
Pinagpala torta delivery.

112
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:46,062
Cut, sir. Cut it out, sir. Yes.

113
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,147
You, sir!

114
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,982
I know what you're doing.

115
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:52,276
It's already 2026!

116
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,986
I'm aware of those tricks.

117
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:57,198
Just because you know that
I find you super duper handsome,

118
00:10:57,281 --> 00:10:59,617
you're taking advantage of it, huh?

119
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,369
Oh, you. As if.

120
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:04,121
You think that with all your charm,

121
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:08,209
I'd just suddenly jump ship
and join your side,

122
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:09,835
just like that?

123
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,837
Oh, no!

124
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:14,423
Because I, Bechay of Cebu,

125
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,801
do solemnly swear my loyalty

126
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:19,220
to the Pinagpala family
forever and ever, amen!

127
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:24,892
You know,

128
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,728
you're such a beautiful brunette, so much,

129
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:30,481
but you're also very smart.

130
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:34,193
I'm just curious.

131
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:37,029
Why are you so loyal to the Pinagpalas?

132
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:39,782
I'm sure in a place like this,

133
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:43,285
there are families that are
more influential, wealthier,

134
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,413
and have businesses where you could work.

135
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:48,457
What is it about that family
that makes you so loyal to them?

136
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,750
It's simple.

137
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:52,420
They're good people.

138
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:56,298
You don't need a long essay
or some complicated reason

139
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,467
to stand on the side
of what's right. Isn't it?

140
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:01,220
Did you know?

141
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:03,305
People here absolutely love them.

142
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:09,061
They never needed a government position
to help other people.

143
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,772
In their own simple way,

144
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:15,568
the good things they've done
have left a mark on this community.

145
00:12:16,485 --> 00:12:17,695
As for me,

146
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:19,822
before my glow-up,

147
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:22,950
and before I became known as Bechay,

148
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:26,495
I started out with nowhere to stay.

149
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:28,998
Because I was an orphan.

150
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,918
Not one of my relatives took me in.

151
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:35,171
Only the Pinagpalas did.

152
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:38,340
They didn't just open their home to me.

153
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:41,218
They also opened their kindest hearts.

154
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:43,012
Especially Mikoy.

155
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:45,931
Oh my, he's practically
like a brother to me.

156
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:50,186
Oh, no.

157
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:52,605
He's crying! He's crying!

158
00:12:52,688 --> 00:12:53,856
See? It worked.

159
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:56,108
- My story was supposed to be
- No!

160
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:57,985
- primetime-worthy.
- What are you talking about?

161
00:12:58,068 --> 00:13:00,362
It's just my rhinitis acting up.

162
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:02,531
- Here.
- Wait.

163
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:05,117
This works for my allergic rhinitis.

164
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:06,035
Liniment.

165
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,954
You can have it. My gift to you.

166
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:36,690
Do we really have to leave right away?

167
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:46,325
Are you sure? Why?

168
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:48,327
Did someone see you?

169
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:55,125
I had a strange feeling earlier.

170
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,712
I thought someone was following me.

171
00:14:30,911 --> 00:14:32,204
Are you sure?

172
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:38,127
Well, if you're sure,
then it's not a problem.

173
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:39,795
We can leave.

174
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:45,301
Something tells me we're not safe here.

175
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,687
There's nothing wrong with overreacting.

176
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:59,023
Chiara, this is your world.

177
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:00,900
You know more about this than I do, okay?

178
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,569
So we will always follow your instincts.

179
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:26,550
You know?

180
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:30,054
We've only just started here.

181
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:34,892
Do you know how hard it is to run
and start over somewhere else?

182
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:39,104
But if that's really how you feel,
then okay.

183
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:41,398
Let's just leave.

184
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,936
Actually, I haven't really seen
anything yet that could

185
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:22,064
put our lives at risk here.

186
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,192
You know,

187
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:29,154
that's why I always admire you,

188
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:32,324
because I know how difficult and chaotic

189
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:34,410
the world you came from is.

190
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:05,232
From now on,

191
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:08,235
stop thinking that you need to protect me.

192
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:09,403
Okay?

193
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:11,113
I should.

194
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:17,369
From now on,
I'll be the one protecting you.

195
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:21,874
I will do everything I can to make sure
nothing bad happens to you.

196
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:23,208
Okay?

197
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:13,801
There's not even a distributor.

198
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,677
It's not even available on seller markets.

199
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:17,805
Are you sure?

200
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,355
Wait. Who gave that to you?

201
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:28,649
The people from the Pinagpala family.

202
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:33,737
<i>Are you going to tell Agent Alex?</i>

203
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,240
<i>Wait, then…</i>

204
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:39,284
She'll be able to find Mikoy.
What about your love team?

205
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,996
Dara, do you really think that's
what I'm worried about right now?

206
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,457
Then I guess not.

207
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,710
<i>Isn't it ironic? If I'm right,</i>

208
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:51,380
deep down, you really don't want
Mikoy to be found.

209
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,090
But in the end,

210
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:55,217
you'll be the one who find him.

211
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,511
Bye!

212
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,222
What an idiot.

213
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,525
That is a futile exercise.

214
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:13,861
You won't get anything from them.

215
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:16,822
Everyone here is loyal to the Pinagpalas.

216
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,494
Why are you so quiet?

217
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:26,498
Don't tell me you're thinking about
fried chicken again.

218
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:31,461
No.

219
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:33,755
I have something else in mind,

220
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,383
and I'm sure you'll be interested in it.

221
00:19:38,468 --> 00:19:39,428
Jungkook?

222
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:42,472
Jungkook? No!

223
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:48,020
It's Mikoy!

224
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:55,736
Hong Kong?

225
00:19:58,363 --> 00:19:59,865
Wait, what makes you say that?

226
00:19:59,948 --> 00:20:01,909
And how did you come up with that theory?

227
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:04,203
Yes, Mikoy is in Hong Kong.

228
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:16,173
A logical conclusion
based on existing information

229
00:20:16,256 --> 00:20:18,133
and on the observations we have.

230
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:22,471
You know, I don't need
a science lecture refresher.

231
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:25,641
I'm not lecturing you, Bok, okay?

232
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:30,187
Where is it now?

233
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,563
Here's the thing.

234
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,857
Look, this.

235
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:35,901
This liniment

236
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:38,570
is exclusively available in Hong Kong.

237
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:40,906
Even from online resellers
here in the Philippines,

238
00:20:40,989 --> 00:20:42,449
you can't buy this.

239
00:20:42,532 --> 00:20:45,077
If you ever happen to find one,

240
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,120
it's fake, okay?

241
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:50,165
And it's true.
What you said is true. Bechay said

242
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,209
that when it comes to family,

243
00:20:52,292 --> 00:20:55,629
the Pinagpalas are solid.
They always stick together.

244
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:57,005
But imagine,

245
00:20:57,881 --> 00:20:59,883
this is exclusive to Hong Kong.

246
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:04,888
How would people in Cebu
get their hands on this liniment

247
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:09,601
if it's exclusively available
in pharmacies in Hong Kong?

248
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:37,421
Sir, we now have enough
solid leads on Chiara and Mikoy.

249
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,266
What?

250
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,519
Alex went to Hong Kong?

251
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:57,941
For her, there are already
verified leads in the area.

252
00:21:58,025 --> 00:21:59,609
Enough for her to mobilize too.

253
00:22:15,292 --> 00:22:16,960
It's still under minimal circulation, sir.

254
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:19,421
Me, Dara, logistics.

255
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:34,936
so we can avoid any misencounters.

256
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:58,937
Sweetheart. Sweetheart, wake up!
We have to go!

257
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:04,359
- Huh? Why? What happened?
- Get dressed. Hurry!

258
00:24:04,442 --> 00:24:05,944
Wait, what's going on?

259
00:24:06,027 --> 00:24:08,280
We don't have time. We have to go now!

260
00:24:08,363 --> 00:24:09,739
They've found us.

261
00:24:36,349 --> 00:24:38,268
And what exactly is CHENES?

262
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:41,897
Sir, they only use that if there is
coordinated law enforcement in Hong Kong.

263
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:46,151
<i>But I have a strong feeling that this</i>
<i>Code Red is for Mikoy and Chiara.</i>

264
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:49,446
<i>Hey, we have a visitor! Hello!</i>

265
00:24:49,529 --> 00:24:51,072
How's your Dad? Does he know you're here?

266
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:54,659
Actually, I'm applying to your bakery.

267
00:24:54,743 --> 00:24:55,869
Huh?

268
00:24:58,371 --> 00:24:59,289
<i>Is Mikoy here?</i>

269
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:00,999
<i>Is he with Chiara?</i>

270
00:25:01,082 --> 00:25:03,418
You know that I'm not allowed
to help them.

271
00:25:03,501 --> 00:25:06,087
Norberto, we're talking about my son here!

272
00:25:06,171 --> 00:25:09,090
After what I did for you,
this is how you pay me back?

273
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:12,719
I have something in mind
for them to escape in Hong Kong.

274
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:15,847
Are you ready?

275
00:25:20,644 --> 00:25:21,895
Okay.
